children.content: There should be processes for other type of details. E.g. Supplier, Product, Service.
Find a Thing is used for both BaT and CaT. The current assumption is that a unified search experience is feasible.
eOrders: preparation and issuing of an electronic order by the contracting authority/entity and its acceptance by the contractor.
ePayment: electronic payment of the ordered goods, services or works.
eInvoicing: preparation and delivery of an invoice in electronic format.
eCatalogues: electronic supplier catalogue prospect uses used to prepare and submit offers or parts of them.

SR-001 asserts that search results must be filtered by user role.
Source: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/12YWGKNRj32QjpeZdKEcsclPNoeEtKM-tj7TBqTz0HVc/edit#gid=1670369241&range=F12
PR-008: Product reviews are shown either as part of the search result or as details from the Content Store.
